The daily case positivity in Bangladesh against the number of samples tested has dropped to around 4% from the highest positivity rate of around 17% seen in the current wave of the disease (https://dghs-dashboard.com/pages/covid19.php). As indicated in item [A], as part of mass vaccination with a Pfizer vaccine especially made for children, Bangladesh has initiated a COVID-19 mass vaccination in children between 5 and 11 years of age. As part of a trial vaccination for this initiative, a total of 16 schoolchildren received the vaccine on 11 Aug 2022. A mass-scale vaccination in children under this age group is expected to begin in the country on 25 Aug 2022.

